data.name: EmailAddressType_Description
data.value: The EmailAddress scalar type constitutes a valid email address, represented as a UTF-8 character sequence. The scalar follows the specification defined by the HTML Spec https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/input.html#valid-e-mail-address.

data.name: EmailAddressType_InvalidFormat
data.value: EmailAddressType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value does not meet the RFC 5322 specification.

data.name: HexColorType_Description
data.value: The HexColor scalar type represents a valid HexColor color code.

data.name: HexColorType_InvalidFormat
data.value: HexColorType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid HEX color code.

data.name: HslType_Description
data.value: The Hsl scalar type represents a valid CSS HSL color defined in https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-3/#hsl-color.

data.name: HslType_InvalidFormat
data.value: HslType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid CSS HSL color code.

data.name: HslaType_Description
data.value: The Hsla scalar type represents a CSS HSLA color as defined in https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-3/#hsla-color.

data.name: HslaType_InvalidFormat
data.value: HslaType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid CSS HSLA color code.

data.name: MacAddressType_Description
data.value: The `MacAddress` scalar type represents an IEEE 802 48-bit or 64-bit Mac address, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The scalar follows the specifications defined in RFC7042 and RFC7043 respectively.

data.name: MacAddressType_InvalidFormat
data.value: MacAddressType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid MAC address.

data.name: IPv4Type_Description
data.value: The IPv4 scalar type represents a valid IPv4 address as defined in RFC791

data.name: IPv4Type_InvalidFormat
data.value: IPv4Type cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid IPv4 address.

data.name: IPv6Type_Description
data.value: The IPv6 scalar type represents a valid IPv6 address as defined in RFC8064

data.name: IPv6Type_InvalidFormat
data.value: IPv6Type cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid IPv6 address.

data.name: IsbnType_Description
data.value: The ISBN scalar type is an ISBN-10 or ISBN-13 number: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number.

data.name: IsbnType_InvalidFormat
data.value: IsbnType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid ISBN number.

data.name: LatitudeType_Description
data.value: The Latitude scalar type represents represents a valid decimal degrees latitude number.

data.name: LatitudeType_InvalidFormat

data.name: LongitudeType_Description
data.value: The Longitude scalar type is a valid decimal degrees longitude number.

data.name: LongitudeType_InvalidFormat
data.value: LongitudeType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value is not a valid longitude number.

data.name: PhoneNumberType_Description
data.value: The PhoneNumber scalar type represents a value that conforms to the standard E.164 format.

data.name: PhoneNumberType_InvalidFormat
data.value: PhoneNumberType cannot parse the provided value. The provided value does not meet the standard E.164 format.

data.name: RgbType_Description
data.value: The Rgb scalar type represents a valid CSS RGB color as defined in https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value#rgb()_and_rgba().
